  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN163-kilavi"><app><lem>piriviṭai</lem><rdg wit="#C7 #RK">piriviṉkaṇ</rdg></app> vaṟpuṟuttun tōḻikkut talaimaka <app><lem>ḷāṟṟāmai</lem><rdg wit="#C7 #RK">ḷāṟṟāmai mītūrac</rdg></app> colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What SHE said about [her] lack of strength to the confidante who consoled [her] in the time of separation.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN163">
        <l><supplied>viṇ</supplied>ṇatirpu talaiiya <supplied>viravumalar</supplied> kuḻaippat</l>
        <l>taṇmaḻai poḻinta tāḻpeyaṟ ka<supplied>ṭai</supplied>nā</l>
        <l>ḷe<supplied>mi</supplied>ya mākit tuṉi<supplied>yuḷaṅ</supplied> kūrac</l>
        <l>ceṉṟō <supplied>ru</supplied>ḷḷic cilvaḷai nekiḻap</l>
        <l>perunacai yuḷḷamoṭu <supplied>varu</supplied>nacai nōkki</l>
        <l><supplied>viḷiyā</supplied> vevvamō ṭaḷiya ḷeṉṉātu</l>
        <l>kaḷiṟuyirt taṉṉa kaṇṇaḻi tu<supplied>va</supplied>lai</l>
        <l>muḷari kariyu muṉ<supplied>pa</supplied>ṉip pāṉāṭ</l>
        <l>kuṉṟu<supplied>nekiḻp</supplied> paṉṉa <supplied>kuḷi</supplied>rkoḷ vāṭai</l>
        <l>yeṉakkē vantaṉai pōṟi puṉaṟkā</l>
        <l>layiriṭu kuppaiyi ṉeñcunekiḻn taviḻak</l>
        <l>koṭiyōr ceṉṟa tēettu maṭiyā</l>
        <l>tiṉaiyai yākic ceṉmati</l>
        <l>viṉaivitup puṟuna ruḷḷa<supplied>lu</supplied> muṇṭē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>During the last days of lingering rains when cool showers pour, (2)</l>
        <l>so that mixed blossoms sprout to which [showers] were bestowed as the sky shakes, (1)</l>
        <l>while, as we are all alone, disgust abounds in [our] hearts, (3)</l>
        <l>while, remembering him who has gone, the few bangle become loose, (4)</l>
        <l>[you], looking at [my] longing for [his] return, with a greatly longing heart, (5)</l>
        <l>[and yet] not thinking “pitiable is she, with unending distress”, (6)</l>
        <l>at midnight, during the fore-dew when thorny twigs are blackened (8)</l>
        <l>by drops that dwindle on the spot, like an elephant’s sighing, (7)</l>
        <l>as if the hills were shrinking, o cold Northwind, (9)</l>
        <l>you would seem to have come just for me. (10a-c)</l>
        <l>Being like this, go (13)</l>
        <l>without dawdling to the country where [my] cruel one has gone (12)</l>
        <l>in order to soften [and] melt [his] heart, like the heaps of fine sand deposited (11)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">by the flood channels. (10d)</l>
        <l>There is also some memory in him who is in haste because of [his] work. (14)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
